4-36:In a tf idf retrieval function, the tf component reflects the occurrence probability of a term in a document .
4-37:This is a further explanation why we can estimate the idf with a simple P(t|d), since the combined tf idf contains the occurrence probability .
4-38:The containment probability corresponds to a document normalisation (document length normalisation, pivoted document length) and is normally attached to the tf component or the tf idf product .
